# Component Architecture

## Three-Layer System

### Layer 1 — UI Primitives (`src/components/ui/`)
Small, reusable, content-free building blocks. Never hardcode colors — use CSS variables.
```
Button.jsx       — variants: primary | secondary | outline | ghost
Badge.jsx        — variants: default | accent
SectionHeader.jsx — title + subtitle used in every section
Card.jsx         — base card wrapper
Input.jsx        — styled text/email input
Textarea.jsx
Label.jsx
Accordion.jsx    — for FAQ
```

### Layer 2 — Sections (`src/components/sections/`)
Full page sections that compose UI primitives. Never write raw `<button>` — use `<Button>`.
```
Hero.jsx / Services.jsx / Process.jsx / Pricing.jsx / FAQ.jsx / CTA.jsx / Footer.jsx
```

### Layer 3 — Layout (`src/components/layout/`)
```
Header.jsx / MobileNav.jsx
```

## Theming
All values reference CSS variables from `globals.css`. Never hardcode colors, fonts, or spacing.

**Available tokens:**
- Colors: `--color-bg`, `--color-surface`, `--color-surface-2`, `--color-border`, `--color-primary`, `--color-primary-dark`, `--color-text`, `--color-muted`
- Fonts: `--font-sans`, `--font-heading`
- Spacing: `--spacing-section`
- Radius: `--radius-sm`, `--radius-md`, `--radius-lg`, `--radius-xl`
- Shadows: `--shadow-card`, `--shadow-glow`

```jsx
/* ✅ GOOD */
<section className="bg-bg py-[var(--spacing-section)]">
<h2 className="font-heading text-primary">

/* ❌ BAD */
<section className="bg-[#09090f] py-24">
<h2 className="font-syne text-amber-500">
```

## Client / Server
- Default to Server Components
- Add `'use client'` only when using hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs
- Never add `'use client'` just because it feels familiar
